\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Integrity}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\lang9\langfe1033\langnp9\insrsid12406749 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\lang9\langfe1033\langnp9\insrsid6447502\charrsid12406749 
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 High, with ACID (Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, Durability) compliance.\tab Lower; often uses BASE (Basically Available, Soft state, Eventually consistent).
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Query Language\tab SQL.\tab Varies (e.g., JSON-based query languages).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\lang9\langfe1033\langnp9\insrsid12406749 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Scalability }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\lang9\langfe1033\langnp9\insrsid6447502\charrsid12406749 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
Traditionally scaled ver\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 tically (more powerful server), but can also scale horizontally.\tab Designed for horizontal scaling (distributing data across many servers).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\lang9\langfe1033\langnp9\insrsid12406749 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Best For\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\lang9\langfe1033\langnp9\insrsid6447502\charrsid12406749 
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Structured data with complex relationships (e.g., financial systems, e-commerce).\tab Unstructured or semi-struct\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 ured data (e.g., social media feeds, IoT data).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \b\f0\ul\lang9\langfe1033\langnp9\insrsid6447502\charrsid12406749 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\sa200\sl276\slmult1\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af31507\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs22\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af31506\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f0\ul\lang9\langfe1033\langnp9\insrsid6447502\charrsid12406749 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 1.3 Introduction to the NoSQL database
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\lang9\langfe1033\langnp9\insrsid6447502\charrsid12406749 \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
NoSQL, or "not only SQL," databases are a class of non-relational database management systems that store data in formats other than the traditional tabular structure use\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
d by relational databases. They are designed for modern applications that require flexible schemas, massive scalability, and high performance, especially when dealing with large volumes of unstructured or semi-structured data.
