 Schema: Unlike a relational database that requires a predefined schema, NoSQL databases are schemaless or have flexible schemas. This allows developers to add new fields or change the data structure without altering the entire database, making them ideal
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 for agile development.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
Horizontal Scalability: NoSQL databases are built to scale horizontally (scale out) by adding more servers to a distributed network, rather than vertically (scale up) by upgrading a single, more powerful server. This makes them high
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 ly effective for handling big data and high-traffic applications.
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Variety of Data Models: NoSQL is an umbrella term for several different types of databases, each with a unique data model optimized for specific use cases. This is a core reason they are so\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
 popular.
